The President is scheduled to travel to Moscow, Russia from July 6 to 8 at the invitation of President Medvedev. The summit meeting will focus on reducing nuclear weapons, cooperating on non-proliferation, exploring missile defense cooperation, addressing mutual threats and security challenges, and expanding ties between the US and Russia. After that, the President will attend the G-8 Summit in L'Aquila, Italy from July 8 to 10, where he will engage with world leaders on various issues. The President will also chair a meeting of the Major Economies Forum on Energy and Climate during this time. Finally, the President and Mrs. Obama will visit Accra, Ghana from July 10 to 11, where they will discuss bilateral and regional issues with Ghanaian President Mills and strengthen the US relationship with Ghana.